# Backend Conventions

## Laravel

- Laravel 12 with PHP 8.4
- Inertia.js for SPA-style routing (Vue frontend)
- Laravel Breeze for authentication
- MySQL database

## Laravel Sail (Local Dev)

All backend commands run **inside Sail** — no local PHP required.

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `make up` | Start containers |
| `make down` | Stop containers |
| `make shell` | Enter Sail shell (for `php artisan`, `composer`) |
| `make db-reset` | `migrate:fresh --seed` |
| `make mysql` | MySQL CLI as root |
| `make pint` | Laravel Pint (code style) |
| `make stan` | PHPStan (static analysis, level 4) |

## Pint & PHPStan

- **Pint**: Laravel's PHP code style fixer. Run `make pint` to auto-fix style issues.
- **PHPStan** (via Larastan): Static analysis. Config in `phpstan.neon` (level 4). Run `make stan` to analyse `app/`.

**Examples:**
- Artisan: `./vendor/bin/sail artisan <command>` or `make shell` then `php artisan`
- Composer: `./vendor/bin/sail composer <command>`
- NPM: `./vendor/bin/sail npm run build`

Use `make shell` when running multiple artisan/composer commands in sequence.
